Gardner:
<i>That revolver shot</i>

35:53.333 --> 35:54.750
<i>is somewhat of a release.</i>

35:56.834 --> 35:59.375
When Jesse fires that gun,

35:59.375 --> 36:03.542
there's a welled-up bitterness
that's been boiling for years.

36:03.542 --> 36:06.834
<i>He still has the memories</i>
<i>he witnessed personally</i>
<i>during the war.</i>

36:06.875 --> 36:08.792
<i>Lots of his friends</i>
<i>have been killed.</i>

36:10.500 --> 36:11.834
Jesse refused to forget.

36:11.834 --> 36:14.709
<i>A lot of his makeup</i>
<i>was revenge.</i>

36:16.417 --> 36:17.709
Come on, Jesse.
We got to go.

36:17.750 --> 36:19.583
Jesse, come on.
Come on, now.

36:19.583 --> 36:21.500
Get, boys, get.

36:34.875 --> 36:36.500
( clicks tongue )
Come on.

36:38.750 --> 36:40.583
Come on.

36:53.375 --> 36:55.875
( hammer clicks,
gunshot )

36:55.875 --> 36:58.417
Narrator:
<i>Jesse James</i>
<i>has just pulled off</i>

36:58.417 --> 37:00.667
<i>one of the first</i>
<i>bank robberies in America,</i>

37:00.667 --> 37:04.583
<i>leaving one man dead</i>
<i>and earning the ex-Confederate</i>

37:04.583 --> 37:06.667
<i>his first victory</i>
<i>against the North.</i>

37:06.667 --> 37:08.834
A lot of the guys
who became outlaws,

37:08.834 --> 37:11.917
Jesse James and so forth,
they were all part of
the Confederate Army.

37:11.917 --> 37:14.583
<i> And when the Union</i>
<i> won that war,</i>

37:14.583 --> 37:16.583
robbing banks
was their way

37:16.583 --> 37:19.875
of continuing the fight
of the Confederacy.

37:19.875 --> 37:22.792
Narrator:
<i> The crime makes headlines</i>
<i> across the state,</i>

37:22.792 --> 37:26.542
<i> turning Jesse</i>
<i> into a wanted criminal.</i>

37:26.542 --> 37:28.500
All right,
it's on you, Frank.

37:28.500 --> 37:30.458
There it is.
( laughs )

37:30.458 --> 37:34.750
It's a good day
to be Frank James,
you know.

37:34.750 --> 37:37.667
Sutherland:
<i>Jesse James certainly had</i>
<i>a very specific idea.</i>

37:37.667 --> 37:40.917
He was going to take the money
that he felt was taken from him
during the Civil War.

37:40.917 --> 37:43.583
<i> The press</i>
<i> got wind of that.</i>

37:43.583 --> 37:46.458
And once they started
reading their own stuff,

37:46.458 --> 37:48.625
they were, "Yeah, I'm right.
You know, I was questioning

37:48.625 --> 37:51.458
whether or not I should have
robbed that bank, but now
I know I'm right."

37:51.458 --> 37:52.834
( laughs )

37:52.834 --> 37:54.917
Narrator:
<i>With his reputation growing,</i>

37:54.917 --> 37:58.792
<i>Jesse James is fanning</i>
<i>the flames of rebellion</i>
<i>in the South.</i>

38:01.875 --> 38:04.500
<i>Over 400 miles away,</i>

38:04.500 --> 38:07.583
<i>the US government is dealing</i>
<i>with an even greater problem</i>

38:07.583 --> 38:09.709
<i>than southern uprisings...</i>

38:12.583 --> 38:15.709
<i>as Indian attacks</i>
<i>by warriors like Crazy Horse</i>

38:15.709 --> 38:18.001
<i>are slowing down</i>
<i>western progress.</i>

38:22.959 --> 38:25.917
<i> But General</i>
<i> Ulysses S. Grant</i>
<i> has an answer--</i>

38:25.917 --> 38:29.959
<i> Civil War hero</i>
<i> George Armstrong Custer.</i>

38:33.792 --> 38:37.959
Grant was quite happy
with the performance of Custer.

38:38.001 --> 38:43.709
<i> Custer was one</i>
<i> of the great heroes</i>
<i> during the Civil War.</i>

38:43.709 --> 38:45.959
<i> He was also willing to do</i>
<i> whatever was necessary</i>

38:45.959 --> 38:48.792
to deal with the Indian issue
right now.

38:50.709 --> 38:52.750
Narrator:
<i> For Custer,</i>
<i> it's the opportunity</i>

38:52.750 --> 38:56.041
<i> he's been waiting for to step</i>
<i> back into the spotlight.</i>

39:02.667 --> 39:05.750
<i> For months, Custer has been</i>
<i> hunting bands of Indians</i>

39:05.750 --> 39:07.542
<i> across</i>
<i> the southern plains...</i>

39:07.542 --> 39:09.959
Halt!

39:09.959 --> 39:12.625
<i>...but hasn't been able</i>
<i>to track them down.</i>

39:19.000 --> 39:21.834
Gardner:
<i>I think Custer had</i>
<i>the same ambitions</i>

39:21.834 --> 39:24.792
that any long-term
military officer had.

39:24.792 --> 39:26.792
That was to advance
in rank.

39:26.792 --> 39:30.917
<i> Advance in rank</i>
<i> and to win laurels,</i>
<i> win glory.</i>

39:30.917 --> 39:34.792
<i> That was hard to do</i>
<i> in the post-Civil War West.</i>

39:34.792 --> 39:37.001
<i> I mean, you weren't meeting</i>
<i> a foe that was lined up</i>

39:37.001 --> 39:39.792
with 10,000 men
on the field of battle.

39:39.792 --> 39:42.709
You were meeting
a very elusive foe.

39:42.709 --> 39:45.875
<i> So I think Custer</i>
<i> was frustrated often</i>

39:45.875 --> 39:49.709
<i> with what he wanted to do,</i>
<i> and I think he wanted glory.</i>

39:54.959 --> 39:58.750
Narrator:
<i> Finally, Custer</i>
<i> catches a break.</i>

40:14.917 --> 40:18.917
<i> His regiment discovers</i>
<i> a band of Cheyenne Indians</i>

40:18.917 --> 40:20.917
<i> camped near</i>
<i> the Washita River</i>

40:20.917 --> 40:24.834
<i> suspected of attacking</i>
<i> settlers and troops.</i>

40:26.041 --> 40:28.000
Get the men ready.

40:28.000 --> 40:29.875
Half an hour.

40:30.917 --> 40:34.041
I want to hit them
with everything we've got.

40:37.667 --> 40:39.041
You have your orders.

40:39.041 --> 40:41.001
Yes, sir.

40:50.834 --> 40:53.750
Narrator:
<i>Desperate for another</i>
<i>chance at greatness,</i>

40:53.750 --> 40:56.625
<i>Custer prepares</i>
<i>a surprise attack.</i>

41:01.041 --> 41:04.083
Jacoby:
<i>Custer is quite consciously,</i>
<i>I think, very aggressive</i>

41:04.125 --> 41:06.709
<i>in his war against Indians</i>

41:06.709 --> 41:08.959
because he's really trying
to reclaim the glory

41:08.959 --> 41:10.792
that he experienced
during the Civil War

41:10.792 --> 41:13.625
<i> when he was</i>
<i> this American hero.</i>

41:24.125 --> 41:27.834
Narrator:
<i> It's only been three years</i>
<i> since the Civil War ended.</i>

41:31.083 --> 41:34.750
<i> But now with Custer</i>
<i> riding into a battle</i>
<i> for glory...</i>

41:38.709 --> 41:41.667
<i> and Jesse James inciting</i>
<i> a rebellion in the South...</i>

41:43.917 --> 41:48.542
<i> America is on the brink</i>
<i> of fighting a two-front war.</i>
